    "about": {
        "title": "About",
        "p1": "Ph.D. in Engineering. Lecturer (2019–2024), Associate Professor (2024–). Funded by CSC for doctoral study, earned M.S. and Ph.D. from Waseda University in 2014 and 2019. Worked at MSRA, Toshiba Global R&D, and NTT Communication Science Labs. 30+ papers in EMNLP, COLING, CogSci, etc., including 25+ in SCI/SSCI/A&HCI indexed journals or CCF-recommended venues. PI of a Shanghai Sci&Tech Commission program (completed) and NSFC Youth project (AI-X); led 5 industry collaborations. Served as PC/Reviewer for ICLR, ICML, NeurIPS, ACL, EMNLP, AAAI, and journals such as TKDD, TNNLS, NLE. Research areas: AI, human–AI collaborative cognition, and NLP (incl. medical documents).",
        "p2": "We primarily welcome students with NLP backgrounds, and also those from linguistics, cognitive science, and psychology. International students are also welcome."
    },
